\begin_layout Standard
Using this method, we were able to identify significant differential binding
 sites from the binned read scores.
 By merging nearby windows that pass the adjusted p-values we get a picture
 of true differential binding sites.
 This analysis is not based on any previous assumptions about the distribution
 of peaks, however the cutoff of what p-values are significant is heuristic.
 We don't do any multiple-corrections and simply look at the top 5000 p-values
 and merge nearby sites.
 After merging nearby windows less than 20bp apart from each other we obtain
 1100 unique significant differential sites.
